The account menu "might not" work unless they actually switch to Gnosis.

I thinkwe can expose the chain config anytime a wallet is connected (not minding which chain the user is connected to). This means all read operations will default to the DEFAULT chain (Gnosis on production, Foundry on local). We will still maintain the `UNSUPPORTED_CHAIN` for write operations when a user is connected to other chains.
```typescript
export type TUserConnected = {
  status: "CONNECTED";
  address: Hex;
  config: ChainConfiguration;
  chain: Chain;
  features: Features;
};
export type TUnsupportedChain = {
  status: "UNSUPPORTED_CHAIN";
  address: Hex;
  chain: Chain;
  features: Features;
};
```

This way, the user will be forced to switch their network before making any write operation.

